# Implementation Plan

[Overview]
Update the rules file to enforce token estimation and tracking.

The goal is to update the core multi-agent workflow specification (`clinerules.base.md`) to explicitly mandate token consumption tracking. Agents will estimate token usage prior to each step (using heuristics based on file size and operation complexity), track the actual token consumption as reported by `winkr query` or `winkr change`, and compare them at the end of each workflow. If a significant discrepancy (+/- 25%) occurs, the agent will analyze the underlying cause. If the findings highlight inefficiencies, the agent will consider formulating an actionable improvement to the rules or operations. This promotes continuous optimization of agent context size and cost efficiency.

